benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/versions - Retrieve a list of catalog versions

covered: Valid Request: Multiple successful retrieval scenarios (global and account-scoped) with assertions on 200 status, content-type, JSON array body and ISO 8601 date-time strings (TC01, TC02, TC14).
Empty Response: Explicit scenarios for no-data (TC03, TC13) assert 200 and empty JSON array.

Query Parameters: Good coverage of accountId variations — valid, non-existent, invalid format, empty, leading/trailing spaces, mixed-case, unsupported extra params, and SQL injection attempt (TC02, TC04, TC05, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC09, TC12).
Authorization: Authentication absence and invalid/expired token scenarios are present and expect 401 (TC06, TC07).
Error Handling: Service unavailable and downstream timeout behaviour covered (TC08, TC11) and malformed JSON/server error covered (TC19).
Security: SQL injection attempt tested and checks for no sensitive data exposure (TC12).
Performance / Load: Large dataset and concurrent request scenarios included (TC10, TC15) with response-time and resource utilization checks.
Regression and Backward Compatibility: Regression test for empty response and backward compatibility test for older clients included (TC13, TC14).
Content-type / Accessibility: Content-type and machine-readable JSON assertions present (TC01, TC20).
gaps: Pagination: No tests verify pagination, offsets, limits, or behavior for paged responses for large datasets (even though large dataset count is tested, pagination mechanics are not).
Caching Behavior: No scenarios assert caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests cover rate limits, 429 responses, or backend throttling under repeated rapid requests aside from concurrency acceptance criteria.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: requests with limit/offset (or page/size), verify correct slicing, total counts (if provided), and behavior at boundaries (last page, beyond last page).
Add caching/conditional request tests: verify presence and correctness of ETag and Cache-Control headers, and behavior for If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since (expect 304 when unchanged).
Add rate-limiting tests: burst requests to verify 429 handling, Retry-After header, and backoff behavior. Include tests for client behavior under 429.
Expand authorization tests to cover 403 where applicable (e.g., authenticated but unauthorized tenant access) and verify explicit error payload shape/fields for auth errors.

Add assertive schema/contract checks: verify array element uniqueness, ordering (if there is an expected order), and explicit response schema validation (types and fields), including max response size checks for large payloads.
